document_data.Description:
The most common use of cable referred to immensely thick and strong ropes, such as thigh-thick hawsers used for mooring and anchoring large [[ship]]s or the lines used to support the movements of massive mechanisms.

A less common form of cable found in the [[Realms]] was a thinner, lighter construction made of a thick twisted [[wire]] with rope woven around it. It was extremely strong for its weight, able to hold surprising amounts of weight, and highly resistant to cutting thanks to the core.

A rare form of cable was wholly made of metal or another material, without including any woven rope.{{Cite dragon/220/Bazaar of the Bizarre: Elven magic|82}}{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|?|4}}
